cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB 

This paper deals with computational measures of semantic similarity between geographic terms, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). The paper discusses the challenge of selecting the most appropriate measure for a specific task, which is a common issue in these sub-fields. Therefore, it is likely that this paper belongs to one or more of these sub-categories.
